    <question id="Emotional Regulation Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 4, where 0 is never, 1 is 'almost never', 2 is 'sometimes', 3 is 'fairly often', and 4 is 'very often', how often you experienced the following feelings during the last month: [Likert 0–4]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Upset by Unexpected Events">how often have you been upset because of something that happened unexpectedly?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Control Important Things">how often have you felt that you were unable to control the important things in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Nervous and Stressed">how often have you felt nervous and stressed?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Lacked Confidence Handling Problems">how often have you felt confident about your ability to handle your personal problems?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Things Going Your Way">how often have you felt that things were going your way?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Cope">how often have you found that you could not cope with all the things that you had to do?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritated by Life">how often have you been able to control irritations in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="On Top of Things">how often have you felt that you were on top of things?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Angered by Uncontrollable Events">how often have you been angered because of things that happened that were outside of your control?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Felt Overwhelmed">how often have you felt difficulties were piling up so high that you could not overcome them?</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>

      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state.       <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Feeling Nervous or On Edge">Feeling nervous, anxious, or on edge</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Uncontrollable Worrying">Not being able to stop or control worrying</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Trouble Relaxing">Trouble relaxing</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Restlessness">Being so restless that it is hard to sit still</sub_question>

    </question>

      <sub_questions>

        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Trouble Relaxing">Trouble relaxing</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Restlessness">Being so restless that it is hard to sit still</sub_question>

    <question id="Parental Education">
      <base_question>How many years of education did your parents receive? [Open-ended]</base_question>

        <sub_question id="Father">Father?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Mother">Mother?</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Life satisfaction">In general, how satisfied are you with all aspects of your life? [Likert 0–10: 0 = Not satisfied, 10 = Totally satisfied]</question>
    <question id="Happiness">How happy did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Laughter">How much did you laugh yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Learning">Did you learn new or exciting things yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Enjoyment">How much did you enjoy the activities you did yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Worry">How worried did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Depression">How depressed did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Anger">How angry did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Stress">How much stress did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Loneliness">How lonely or unsupported did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Emotional Regulation Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 4, where 0 is never, 1 is 'almost never', 2 is 'sometimes', 3 is 'fairly often', and 4 is 'very often', how often you experienced the following feelings during the last month: [Likert 0–4]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Upset by Unexpected Events">how often have you been upset because of something that happened unexpectedly?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Control Important Things">how often have you felt that you were unable to control the important things in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Nervous and Stressed">how often have you felt nervous and stressed?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Lacked Confidence Handling Problems">how often have you felt confident about your ability to handle your personal problems?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Things Going Your Way">how often have you felt that things were going your way?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Cope">how often have you found that you could not cope with all the things that you had to do?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritated by Life">how often have you been able to control irritations in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="On Top of Things">how often have you felt that you were on top of things?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Angered by Uncontrollable Events">how often have you been angered because of things that happened that were outside of your control?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Felt Overwhelmed">how often have you felt difficulties were piling up so high that you could not overcome them?</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Anxiety Symptoms Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 3, where 0 is 'Not at all', 1 is 'several days', 2 is 'more than half of the days', and 3 is 'Nearly every day'. Over the last two weeks, how often have you been bothered by the following problems? [Likert 0–3]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Feeling Nervous or On Edge">Feeling nervous, anxious, or on edge</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Uncontrollable Worrying">Not being able to stop or control worrying</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Trouble Relaxing">Trouble relaxing</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Restlessness">Being so restless that it is hard to sit still</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritability">Becoming easily annoyed or irritable</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Fear Something Awful Might Happen">Feeling afraid, as if something awful might happen</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Depressive Symptoms Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 3, where 0 is 'Not at all', 1 is 'several days', 2 is 'more than half of the days', and 3 is 'Nearly every day'. Over the last two weeks, how often have you been bothered by the following problems?</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Anhedonia">Little interest or pleasure in doing things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Depressed Mood">Feeling down, depressed, or hopeless</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Sleep Problems">Trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Fatigue">Feeling tired or having little energy</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Appetite Changes">Poor appetite or overeating</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Feelings of Worthlessness">Feeling bad about yourself or that you are a failure or have let yourself or your family down</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Concentration Difficulties">Trouble concentrating on things, such as reading the newspaper or watching television</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Psychomotor Changes">Moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed. Or the opposite — being so fidgety or restless that you have been moving around a lot more than usual</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Suicidal Thoughts">Thoughts that you would be better off dead, or of hurting yourself</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
  </questions>

      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Life satisfaction">In general, how satisfied are you with all aspects of your life? [Likert 0–10: 0 = Not satisfied, 10 = Totally satisfied]</question>
    <question id="Happiness">How happy did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Laughter">How much did you laugh yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Learning">Did you learn new or exciting things yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Enjoyment">How much did you enjoy the activities you did yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Worry">How worried did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Depression">How depressed did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Anger">How angry did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Stress">How much stress did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Loneliness">How lonely or unsupported did you feel yesterday? [Likert 0–10: 0 = At no time, 10 = All the time]</question>
    <question id="Emotional Regulation Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 4, where 0 is never, 1 is 'almost never', 2 is 'sometimes', 3 is 'fairly often', and 4 is 'very often', how often you experienced the following feelings during the last month: [Likert 0–4]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Upset by Unexpected Events">how often have you been upset because of something that happened unexpectedly?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Control Important Things">how often have you felt that you were unable to control the important things in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Nervous and Stressed">how often have you felt nervous and stressed?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Lacked Confidence Handling Problems">how often have you felt confident about your ability to handle your personal problems?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Things Going Your Way">how often have you felt that things were going your way?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Cope">how often have you found that you could not cope with all the things that you had to do?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritated by Life">how often have you been able to control irritations in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="On Top of Things">how often have you felt that you were on top of things?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Angered by Uncontrollable Events">how often have you been angered because of things that happened that were outside of your control?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Felt Overwhelmed">how often have you felt difficulties were piling up so high that you could not overcome them?</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Anxiety Symptoms Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 3, where 0 is 'Not at all', 1 is 'several days', 2 is 'more than half of the days', and 3 is 'Nearly every day'. Over the last two weeks, how often have you been bothered by the following problems? [Likert 0–3]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Feeling Nervous or On Edge">Feeling nervous, anxious, or on edge</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Uncontrollable Worrying">Not being able to stop or control worrying</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Trouble Relaxing">Trouble relaxing</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Restlessness">Being so restless that it is hard to sit still</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritability">Becoming easily annoyed or irritable</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Fear Something Awful Might Happen">Feeling afraid, as if something awful might happen</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Depressive Symptoms Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 3, where 0 is 'Not at all', 1 is 'several days', 2 is 'more than half of the days', and 3 is 'Nearly every day'. Over the last two weeks, how often have you been bothered by the following problems?</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Anhedonia">Little interest or pleasure in doing things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Depressed Mood">Feeling down, depressed, or hopeless</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Sleep Problems">Trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Fatigue">Feeling tired or having little energy</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Appetite Changes">Poor appetite or overeating</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Feelings of Worthlessness">Feeling bad about yourself or that you are a failure or have let yourself or your family down</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Concentration Difficulties">Trouble concentrating on things, such as reading the newspaper or watching television</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Psychomotor Changes">Moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed. Or the opposite — being so fidgety or restless that you have been moving around a lot more than usual</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Suicidal Thoughts">Thoughts that you would be better off dead, or of hurting yourself</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>

      <sub_questions>

        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>

        <sub_question id="Restlessness">Being so restless that it is hard to sit still</sub_question>

    <question id="Emotional Regulation Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 4, where 0 is never, 1 is 'almost never', 2 is 'sometimes', 3 is 'fairly often', and 4 is 'very often', how often you experienced the following feelings during the last month: [Likert 0–4]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Upset by Unexpected Events">how often have you been upset because of something that happened unexpectedly?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Control Important Things">how often have you felt that you were unable to control the important things in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Nervous and Stressed">how often have you felt nervous and stressed?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Lacked Confidence Handling Problems">how often have you felt confident about your ability to handle your personal problems?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Things Going Your Way">how often have you felt that things were going your way?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Unable to Cope">how often have you found that you could not cope with all the things that you had to do?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritated by Life">how often have you been able to control irritations in your life?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="On Top of Things">how often have you felt that you were on top of things?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Angered by Uncontrollable Events">how often have you been angered because of things that happened that were outside of your control?</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Felt Overwhelmed">how often have you felt difficulties were piling up so high that you could not overcome them?</sub_question>
      </sub_questions>
    </question>
    <question id="Anxiety Symptoms Frequency">
      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state.       <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Feeling Nervous or On Edge">Feeling nervous, anxious, or on edge</sub_question>

        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Trouble Relaxing">Trouble relaxing</sub_question>

    </question>

Respondents with a 'Happiness' score higher than the average are:

      <base_question>Next, you will be asked questions about your emotional state. Please answer on a scale of 0 to 3, where 0 is 'Not at all', 1 is 'several days', 2 is 'more than half of the days', and 3 is 'Nearly every day'. Over the last two weeks, how often have you been bothered by the following problems? [Likert 0–3]</base_question>
      <sub_questions>
        <sub_question id="Feeling Nervous or On Edge">Feeling nervous, anxious, or on edge</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Uncontrollable Worrying">Not being able to stop or control worrying</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Excessive Worry">Worrying too much about different things</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Trouble Relaxing">Trouble relaxing</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Restlessness">Being so restless that it is hard to sit still</sub_question>
        <sub_question id="Irritability">Becoming easily annoyed or irritable</sub_question>
